title.narrative: Programme de développement du titre II d'USAID par le développement adventiste et organisme d'aide humanitaire international.

description.narrative: (Madagascar): The Adventist Development and Relief Agency (ADRA) is USAID's implementing partner for Asotry, an integrated food security activity that reduces food insecurity and vulnerability among food insecure households and communities. Asotry targets women of reproductive age, children under five, subsistence farmers and their communities, with special attention paid to adolescents and youth, the elderly, and the disabled, in the targeted regions of Amoron'i Mania, Haute Matsiatra, and Atsimo Andrefana. With FY 2018 funds, Asotry will provide training to local government officials and community volunteers in health, agriculture and disaster risk reduction activities to support project sustainability in preparation for project closeout in September 2019. The activity will finish distributing food commodities to children under two, complete construction and rehabilitation of wells, feeder roads and other infrastructure, and strengthen linkages between farmers and private sector actors to sustainably increase rural incomes. In addition, Asotry will work on a smooth closure of the project ensuring all administrative and legal rights and obligations related to staffing, reporting and assets disposal are met and performed in a timely manner. This activity aligns with the U.S. Government Global Food Security Strategy and its goals to generate inclusive and sustainable agriculture-led economic growth; strengthen resilience among people and systems; and ensure a well-nourished population. ADRA has a long standing presence in the intervention zones and core competence and extensive experience in implementing food security-related programs in Madagascar.. .. .
